{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6",
    "summary": "Source text for 4 Maccabees 6 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:1",
      "text": "When Eleazar had in this manner answered the exhortations of the tyrant, the spearbearers came up, and rudely dragged Eleazar to the instruments of torture.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:2",
      "text": "First, they stripped the old man, adorned as he was with the beauty of piety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:3",
      "text": "Then tying back his arms and hands, they disdainfully flogged him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:4",
      "text": "A herald opposite cried out, “Obey the commands of the king!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:5",
      "text": "But the high-minded and truly noble Eleazar, as one tortured in a dream, ignored it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:6",
      "text": "But raising his eyes on high to heaven, the old man’s flesh was stripped off by the scourges, and his blood streamed down, and his sides were pierced through.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:7",
      "text": "Falling on the ground from his body having no power to endure the pains, he still kept his reasoning upright and unbending.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:8",
      "text": "Then one of the harsh spearbearers rushed at him and began to kick him in the side to force him to get up again after he fell.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:9",
      "text": "But he endured the pains, despised the cruelty, and persevered through the indignities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:10",
      "text": "Like a noble athlete, the old man, when struck, vanquished his torturers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:11",
      "text": "His face sweating, and he panting for breath, he was admired even by the torturers for his courage.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:12",
      "text": "Therefore, partly in pity for his old age,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:13",
      "text": "partly from the sympathy of acquaintance, and partly in admiration of his endurance, some of the attendants of the king said,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:14",
      "text": "“Why do you unreasonably destroy yourself, O Eleazar, with these miseries?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:15",
      "text": "We will bring you some meat cooked by yourself, and you can save yourself by pretending that you have eaten swine’s flesh.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:16",
      "text": "Eleazar, as though the advice more painfully tortured him, cried out,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:17",
      "text": "“Let us who are children of Abraham not be so evil advised as by giving way to make use of an unbecoming pretense.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:18",
      "text": "For it would be irrational, if having lived up to old age in all truth, and having scrupulously guarded our character for it, we would now turn back",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:19",
      "text": "and ourselves become a pattern of impiety to the young, as being an example of eating pollution.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:20",
      "text": "It would be disgraceful if we would live on some short time, and that scorned by all men for cowardice,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:21",
      "text": "and be condemned by the tyrant for cowardice by not contending to the death for our divine law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:22",
      "text": "Therefore you, O children of Abraham, die nobly for your religion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:23",
      "text": "You spearbearers of the tyrant, why do you linger?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:24",
      "text": "Beholding him so high-minded against misery, and not changing at their pity, they led him to the fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:25",
      "text": "Then with their wickedly contrived instruments they burned him on the fire, and poured stinking fluids down into his nostrils.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:26",
      "text": "He being at length burned down to the bones, and about to expire, raised his eyes Godward, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:27",
      "text": "“You know, O God, that when I might have been saved, I am slain for the sake of the law by tortures of fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:28",
      "text": "Be merciful to your people, and be satisfied with the punishment of me on their account.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:29",
      "text": "Let my blood be a purification for them, and take my life in exchange for theirs.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:30",
      "text": "Thus speaking, the holy man departed, noble in his torments, and even to the agonies of death resisted in his reasoning for the sake of the law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:31",
      "text": "Confessedly, therefore, religious reasoning is master of the emotions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:32",
      "text": "For had the emotions been superior to reasoning, I would have given them the witness of this mastery.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:33",
      "text": "But now, since reasoning conquered the emotions, we befittingly award it the authority of first place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:34",
      "text": "It is only fair that we should allow that the power belongs to reasoning, since it masters external miseries.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.6.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 6:35",
      "text": "It would be ridiculous if it weren’t so. I prove that reasoning has not only mastered pains, but that it is also superior to the pleasures, and withstands them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
